,Recommended,248610,16506975,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,Pomegranate,"One of the best games i've played in a long time, will be perfect for those nostalgic about the old SWAT games. While being highly addictive, its mechanics are extremely simple and easy to understand. Yet there lies a great challenge in executing them flawlessly, and succeding with your objectives without losing any of your men.Lots of content in it in form of single missions, campaigns, mod support and mission generator, so there's essentially an endless amounts of mission to go on. There's also some basic customization to get you a bit emotionally attached to your men (and women). However it seems that there are no female voices, so females will report in with male voices.No mp or coop yet, but I think they are planning to add that after phone versions release.Sidenote: If you use steam overlay a lot keep in mind that the shift key locks the path, so after you've been to the overlay press shift once to make the controls normal again."
,Recommended,248610,11713179,"Posted: 15 August, 2014",all,Snake,"REVERSE WARNING: This is actually the only Early Access game that I bought without regretting it later.Door Kickers is a solid top-down 2D tactical SWAT strategy / tactical / shooter title. You draw your troopers' paths with your mouse, place waypoints and commands and then watch the action unfold according to your plan. There is also the option to pause the action in real-time and switch orders on the fly. The game went through many iterations and improvements during early access, both frequent and meaningful in content and changes / fixes.The biggest draws of the game (apart from the obvious - existing in a great genre that is virtually abandoned) is the fact that it has Steam Workshop support and an integrated level editor allowing for infinite content. When the core gameplay mechanics are as polished and as fun, even simple user-made maps can add tons of replayability to a game that is already quite large in beta form.I bought this game in December 2013 and watched it blossom into the beautiful thing it is today, a couple of months before its final release. I recommend this wholeheartedly to anyone who is interested in the genre."
76561197972382461,Recommended,248610,32605580,Posted: 20 June,all,DoGCyN,"I'm only barely recommending this game as it grates my nipples hard. That final boat campaign mission with the hostages may as well have had me sweating. I was so proud of finishing it I took a screencap, made a backup, and there is a good chance I will frame that screen cap in the near future. You do some of these missions right once, or you spend 30+ minutes doing them all over again...again and again and again.Let me be clear. I hate this game. I absolutely do. I played he campaign to get it out of my backlog for good, hoping it would be better for my tastes as it was heavily recommended for me. As a huge fan of Xcom, FFT, and the Starcraft series, this strategy game had me wanting to punch my monitor. I recommend other strategy game fans try it to see what they think, as the general consensus for this game IS positive. Just not positive enough for me.Graphics: N/A - They're okay but I don't believe the graphics for this title factor into the score. If they did, it would be a solid 8/10. Mostly because they look clean for what they are, but aren't incredible by any means.Sound/Music: 7/10 - Acceptable. I don't think the Dubstep type music you hear in some levels fit the setting very much. The sound effects the characters give are okay. Guns sound nice.Gameplay: 6/10 - Similar to the Xcom series, the gameplay has some dice rolls when it comes to accuracy and possibly damage done to enemies. This is both a good mechanic and a frustrating one, and on some missions, not a whole lot of skill when it comes to strategy comes into play (i.e. the Ambush campaign mission for those who've played it). You have to get a pretty good start in order to have any chance of finishing.It's a nice touch that characters level up and get better stats. You can apparently also name your team (although I did not).I feel like 90% of the weapons are completely useless. I ended up using I think maybe 5 total weapons throughout the game. I tried using other ones but most of them ended up being just pointless and terrible. Perhaps they're implemented to give a bigger challenge on missions? (i.e. ""You have to do this mission using only p90s!"")Shield class isn't very useful. Appears to be best used for missions with low class enemies (enemies that die fast and don't hurt much). Pointman class also feels pointless. Good starting class I suppose.Overall: 6/10 - Yes, a 6. Again, I hate this game. It has flaws that will have me never playing it ever again. However, please try it out if you're reading this and you like strategy games. You may just fall in love with it. Good luck!"
