76561198098730482,Recommended,248610,26284419,"Posted: 29 October, 2016",all,alkali.lake,"This game has been on my wishlist for two holiday sales. Since I usually don't buy any ""wargames"" or straight up shooters I was hesitant to buy it, but finally gave in, when it was 50% off, thinking what's there to loose with the steam refund system?To my astonishment, it's a ""simple"" strategy game and that's just up my alley.Plan your way in with your squad, level them up, get new equipment and defuse dangerous situations: rescue hostages, defuse bombs, kill hostiles, save the day.The game itselfs has a huge amount of levels out of the box and with a superb workshop integration can be expanded indefinitely by community made levels and items. It's also really, really easy to make your own maps as a level editor is already integrated int the game. If you don't want to make anything too fancy (new texture, objects, round rooms) you'll be extremely happy with the in-game options for designing new levels.It really is a steal for any price (if you're looking at this review and the game is also 50% off, don't hesitate and just get it!)Here's the checklist of what you can expect:PROs:+ huge amount of levels+ great replayability (play with different squad members, play with different equipment, play from different entry-zones...)+ adequate learning-curve (easy levels to get used to the mechanics)+ ability to play any level at any chosen time (no unlocking levels, everything is available right from the start, though not every level is a good idea to play right away)+ controls are great with and uncluttered and handy interface+ squad members can be renamed and given their own design+ great steam workshop integration+ integrated level editor+ price for what you get is absolutely adequate+ replay ability from almost any starting point within a levelCONs:- campaign mode needs better warning for what happens to killed squad members (once you've figured it out though, you'll remember forever)- not all stats on items are relevant when equippedOverall: 8/10"
