,Recommended,248610,29951294,Posted: 15 February,all,Dr. Frog ☭☢,"Door Kickers is a top down, tactical, strategy, shooter, hybrid developed by Killhouse Games.The core gameplay of Door Kickers is controlling a squad of trained SWAT team members as you clear out various locations, ranging from drug dens to warehouse's. The player can pause the game and enter planing mode. In this mode the player and set where their team will move and face to cover every angle. In this mode the player can also prep their squad to breach doors, throw grenades and set various other orders. Once the player resumes time the team will do the actions in real-time, the squad can also be controlled in real-time.The story comes from the games campaigns. Each campaign has permadeath for the squad members, so if a squad member dies in the first mission, they will not be available for any other mission, unless the first mission is restarted. Multiple campaigns with different difficulties, lengths and missions add a fair amount of replay value to the game. Campaigns, however, are locked until the player reaches a high enough profile level. Door Kickers also comes with single missions, some being training missions but most being more challenging. A random mission generator is also available. The player can choose the size of the map and how difficult it is, adding even more replay value.Door Kickers has various classes to be unlocked, from shields to breacher's, all with their own tools, weapons, and customizable names. There are well over 100 weapons and tools for the various classes. Players can complete missions any way they see fit, charging in with assault rifles and shields or stealthy with suppressed submachine guns. Players have complete control of how they execute a mission.Door Kickers does a fair amount right:Has a large variety of guns and classesHas great replay value from various maps and game modesAddictiveFantastic sound designThe art style fits wellDoor Kickers does a few things wrong:The player must unlock the campaignThe guns can be expensive to unlockDoesn't keep the player interested over timeCan be to easy/hard based on skill levelSurprisingly hard to remain stealthyOverall Door kickers is a solid title. With a price tag of $21.99CND, it is a bit pricy for someone who doesn't commonly enjoy this genre of game. If Door Kickers goes on sale, pick it up and try it out, it's a great deal of fun and great for killing some time.Have a good one~Doc"
