,Recommended,248610,17242798,"Posted: 26 July, 2015",all,ZeroOne,"Reminds me of Frozen Synapse, which is an excellent game, with the exception that you can pause at any time, or you can choose not to pause ever and just guide your troops in real time. The more difficult missions are like puzzles where you have to manage your limited number of team members but still cover all the possible angles where an enemy might try to take you by surprise. You may also have an additional requirement besides just neutralizing all the enemies (""tangos""), such as saving all the hostages. The situation might be that the enemies will start shooting the hostages in one minute, and you must make your way to them quickly enough, or there might be a time bomb to defuse. On some levels you get sniper support, with the sniper somewhere off the screen, able to shoot any enemy that happens to, say, stand in front of a right (or wrong, for him) window. The game also gives you star ratings for each level, and there are additional achievements, such as completing a level with a single trooper, so I find the replay value is very good. Recommended!"
