76561197971213209,Recommended,248610,11085702,"Posted: 5 July, 2014",all,Shroomie,"With a loud 'crump' the door turned from 50 year old hardwood, into matchsticks in the blink of an eye. In one fluid motion two armed men stormed through the breach, in a coordinated strike, with all the precision of years of training they checked the room for hostiles. ""CLEAR!"" the first officer shouted, echoed a moment later by his partner, following in behind them two more armed police moved into the room, leap frogging their comrades positions to take up covering overwatches.Stacking up either side of the next door, one officer leaned forwards, ready to open the door, the second officer priming a flashbang, pin pulled he looked to his colleague and nodded. Turning the handle and throwing the door open the first officer stood back, raising his sleek compact submachine gun, the second tossing the live grenade into the room, an ear splitting bang, and a blinding flash stunning the hostage taker inside, the officers moved in with lethal grace, one three round burst of fire and the aggressor was down, the second officer kneeling to cheek the hostage was unarmed.Door Kickers is a tense top down tactical simulation game, you control a squad of specialist counter-terrorism/hostage rescue officers. You unlock equipment (and soon traits) with stars awarded for completing the levels with no casualties and under the time limit. The interface is clean and easy to use, the controls slick and intuitive, it takes moments to learn but knowing how to control your team is only the start of it.Learning the best combinations of weapons and tactics will prove harder, the game is unforgiving, but in a good way, when you've made a mistake you'll know it, forget to check a corner? You'll pay for it when the 'empty room' turns out to be hiding a hostile with a Mac-10.The game has just recently entered into Beta stage, and it's well worth the money, bugs are few and far between and it runs well and looks great."
76561197966340890,Recommended,248610,11876197,"Posted: 26 August, 2014",all,tyhDashBoom,"Do you remember Rainbow Six's famous planning phase? Did you enjoy that part of the game more than the actual mission? If you answered yes to these questions, Door Kickers is a worthwhile investment.The game's core features right now are quite good. There is a slight learning curve to get your guys moving the way you want. Sometimes you will feel like you are micromangaging movements especially if you want to execute proper room clearing techniques. And occasionally you get angry at the pathing system since there are numerous house plants and chairs which create impassable barriers. But it is still fun.There are definitely a good number of missions available of varying difficulty. Some you will breeze right through, others will be the bain of your existence until you get that perfect plan with 0 casualties working just right. Also the random mission generator is always good if you are looking for a quick challenge. As well as replaying missions trying to achieve the single-plan and hands-off achievements.The loadouts are varied and offer a decent sized arsenal. It is mostly reflective of what a police SWAT team would have available. One gameplay feature I like is how your team really practices good trigger discipline (single shots if possible). While the bad guys will often go full auto at the slightest of targets. One thing that is not completely apparent in the loadout section of the game is what effects do the equipment have on your team. You'll notice in cramped interiors, it takes the man with the M4 longer to train his rifle than the man weilding his pistol. But for those long corridor or outdoor shots, your Assaulter with his rifle is far more efficient than your rear guard weiding his shotgun. Sadly none of this is explicitly described in the loadout menu and will take some experimentation to figure out what the ideal loadout is based on your style of play and the mission.The graphics and sound are good for a game. It is definitely not a high fidelity sound and graphics visual masterpiece, but that really is not necessary. It is the gameplay which makes this game shine. There are various mods which revamp the sound experience if you are unhappy with the tone of the firearms.Overall, really fun game!"
