,Recommended,248610,32824281,Posted: 26 June,all,Thoroughbred Aryan Loli,"Don't mind my playtime, I've got +60 hours on the DRM-free version (yay GOG). It's a fun tacticool-y top-down shooter with some light RPG progression elements and toggable permadeath. So it is tactical to some extent, but far from grognardy. You won't be punished for executing an imperfect slice of the pie, and that's okay.The pros:Great and easy modability; active workshopPassable gunplay, basic but FUN nonethelessA series of short but engaging campaigns. Whack-load of one-off single missions and tons of maps on the workshop. There's a random level generator too, but it's basic as heck and the basic gameplay turns those levels into a arcadey Robotron-esque experience.The meh:Few and limited art and sound assets, but a-ok quality. There's only one voice for tactical commands and it gets old fast. The character portraits are goofy but nice. You can easily get attached to your dudes and weep over untimely deaths.Weapon and class unlocks are grindy as heck (some people dig this). The basic weapons are good enough, but for the unlockables there's a clear progression - you only achieve a full variety of tactical options after some good grinding. Just mod this out if the grinds turns you off.The cons:Basic, grunt-y AI. You're against mooks and crankheads with tooty shooters, and it shows. At the end of the day this is the game's biggest fault. A good AI (even if it only meant throwing some unexpected punches at you every now and then) would make the game infinitely replayable. As it stands, there's 10-15 hours of gameplay here.VEREDICT:This ain't the love baby of SWAT 4 and Frozen Synapse. If you wanna rock your grognard balls off you'll have to look elsewhere. Some peeps say this is essentially a mobile game, but the devs set the bar a bit higher than that. Think mobile on steroids. If unsure, grab on sale. Otherwise go for it."
