,Recommended,248610,10199929,"Posted: 22 May, 2014",all,WesleySmalls,"Old Rainbow Six/SWAT, with a bit of Hotline Miami goes FTL.Well, that's a rather weird explanation of the game. In sense, it is a top-down fast paced tactical shooter. You don't really ""play"" a person, but rather manage the operation as a overseer. You control an (I assume), SWAT team and plan their movement through various buildings. It shares the pausing of time to plan your move much like FTL does. The way you ravage your team through the environment has quite a lot of similarity with Hotline Miami.The game is really enjoyable and rather fast paced, with short levels(think 30 second operations). Getting it right at first requires a bit of effort and can be challenging, but once you get the hang of it it becomes very enjoyable and pleasing to see your planned route work.The game is in Beta, but for it's state it is very, very featured. Everything regarding planning and working out your entry seems to be there, including loadouts. Outside of that, there still seems to be still a bit less game but I am sure that will change in the future.Reaction to sound seems a bit lacking, and your team seems to lack own thought. They will happely ignore a gunshot next to their head when they haven't spotted the hostile or if the hostile isn't on your path. This is in contrast with the hostiles, which seem to be having much better ears.It's a really fun game and already feels to be worth the price."
