,Recommended,248610,12668370,"Posted: 28 October, 2014",all,Fawkzi,"An absolutely outstanding experience, I've really never played a game like it before.Door Kickers is a top down, Real time strategy game unlike any other i have played before. you control a swat team of various size depending on the mission you pick, you can either chose single missions or play a campaign mode which is a set of specific missions with varying objectives that span all game types. Drug Busts, Hostage Rescue, Elimination, arrest warrant. and so on.You have two ways you can do this, create a plan in the planning phase or just go all out and control the team members in real time (I do not recomend this) The planning is the star of this game, set each individual team members path of movement and direction they are facing, set certain way points such as getting them to hold a certain position until all hostiles in his field of view are dead or getting them to hold a certain position until you give them the go ahead to continue n their pre-planned path.How well this plan is executed however is dependant on the equipment and upgrades you have unlocked. After each mission you are awarded EXP, how much EXP you are awarded is dependant on how many stars you were rated and how many challenges you completed within the mission.EXP goes toward levels which span your entire team, each time you level up you ear stars and points, the stars can be spent on new and better gear where as the points are spent in the skill tree to improve your team members proficiency with certain weapons.the game has classes, at first you just have the ""point Man"" class but you soon start to unlock the others. Assaulter, Shield, Breacher and Stealth. each one unlocking at a specific milestone. when you first start out you'll most likely spend a lot of time replaying old missions to get used to the mechanics but it's when you've unlocked every class that the game really picks up.Customizing your team per mission with the classes certain missions may need.The game comes with a mission creator though the UI in that map creator isn't very helpful, in fact it feels like more of a hinderence, text of items over lap each other to the point where you can't read them and the creator also offers you no help, no explanation on how to use the funtion.it is a very in depth mission creator when you look at everything you are able to place and control but as i said, it offers you no explanation on how to use these things.For example i clicked on the ""Walls"" tool, expecting myself to be able to place walls only for the walls not showing up at all in the test run of the map and since the creator offers you no help, i had no idea why this wasn't happening.All in all i'd give this ame a 7/10 and that 7 comes from the main game alone, the map creator gets a 0 from me purely because it offers you no help what so ever, like it expects you to know how to use everything without ever having used it before."
