76561197987613673,Recommended,248610,31640350,Posted: 8 May,all,[LHI] kaladorn,"Top down entry-team fun! Play it in real time with multiple players (for some laughs and lots of fail) or play it in plan mode as single player and run your team through the entry op.Some are neutralize all hostiles, some are hostage situation, some are hostage with gun to head (easy to lose those), some are stop robberies, defuse explosives, capture information sources, and the list goes on - VIP protection is fun!There are all sorts of locales from a beach house to a parking garage to a country house to pretty much you name it - lots of levels have been created and are available.The operation plans you can create are exceptionally varied and can include conditional actions and pauses to help sync up your team's activities.As you practice, more types of gear opens up for each specialty on the team. Patience is required to get the whole loadout, but you don't need all of the options if you look at what some systems can do (there is some overlap in stats or in uses) and pick carefully.Missions provide up to 3 stars and sometimes getting 2 stars is pretty hard, let alone 3. But then you get better gear eventually, get a better plan, and try again. Eventually you hit on the working combination.You can use a limited amount of stealth once you get lock guns/lock picks, silenced weapons, and a stealth specialist. You can use a bit before all that, but it is easier with all those bits.And it usually pays to be patient and use caution, flashbangs, stingballs, and so on to clear ahead before going in. Sometimes though, with a short time limit, you have to run b*lls-to-the-wall and still arrange not to accidentally kill your own hostage you are trying to save.I don't really have any complaint about this game except that I'd like to see more large maps with outdoor areas. I suppose it would also be nice to see them figure a way to put a police robot into the game (demolitions)."
